contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Reserpine is an adrenergic blocking agent used to treat mild to moderate hypertension via the disruption of norepinephrine vesicular storage The antihypertensive actions of Reserpine are a result of its ability to deplete catecholamines from peripheral sympathetic nerve endings These substances are normally involved in controlling heart rate force of cardiac contraction and peripheral resistance
